{"title_page": "British Bencoolen", "text_new": "{{Infobox former subdivision\n|native_name = \n|common_name = Bencoolen Residency\n|nation      = British India\n|subdivision = Residency\n|era         = \n|year_start  = 1685\n|date_start  = \n|event_start = \n|year_end    = 1824 [[Anglo\u2013Dutch Treaty of 1824|Anglo\u2013Dutch Treaty]]\n|date_end    = \n|event_end   =\n|event1      = \n|date_event1 = \n|p1          = \n|s1          = Dutch East Indies\n|flag_p1     = \n|flag_s1     = Flag of the Netherlands.svg \n|image_flag  = Flag of Great Britain.svg\n|image_coat  = \n|image_map   = File:IndonesiaBengkulu.png\n|image_map_caption = Location of British Bencoolen in present-day Indonesia\n|stat_area1  = \n|stat_year1  = \n|stat_pop1   = \n|today       = {{flag|Indonesia}}\n|footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''British Bencoolen''' was a British possession extending along the southwestern coast of [[Sumatra]] centered on the area of what is now [[Bengkulu City]]. The British [[East India Company]] (EIC) established a presence there in 1685,<ref name=\"Olson1996\"/> and in 1714 the EIC built [[Fort Marlborough]] there, as local datoo allowed EIC to build the fort in order to protect them from the Dutch.\n\nOriginally a [[Presidencies and Provinces of British India|Presidency]] within [[British India]], in 1785 it was downgraded to Bencoolen Residency and placed under the [[Bengal Presidency]].<ref>http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Indonesia.htm#Bencoolen</ref>\n\nOn 15 October 1817, [[Stamford Raffles]] was appointed [[Lieutenant-Governor of Bencoolen]].  During his time as Lieutenant-Governor, Raffles enacted [[Stamford Raffles#Bencoolen (Bengkulu) and Malaya|major reforms]], including the abolition of slavery, as well as creating [[Singapore]] to provide a new trading port in the region.\n\nIn 1823, Singapore was removed from the control of Bencoolen.<ref>Kevin YL Tan. [https://books.google.com/books?id=RqTwXSKrBQMC&pg=PA29&dq=%22Bencoolen%22+presidency&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7WnoUI_YH8Wn4gTshIGIAg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Bencoolen%22%20presidency&f=false ''The Singapore Legal System''].</ref> The British ceded Bencoolen to the [[Netherlands]] in the [[Anglo-Dutch Treaty of 1824]].<ref name=Roberts1>{{cite book|last=Roberts|first=Edmund|title=Embassy to the Eastern Courts of Cochin-China, Siam, and Muscat|year=1837|publisher=Harper &  Brothers|location=New York|page=34|url=http://www.wdl.org/en/item/7317/view/1/34/}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Southern Sumatra, De Grote Winkler Prins Encyclopedia 1910.jpg|thumb|Former British Bencoolen (in pink) on an 1910 map]]\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"Olson1996\">Olson JS, Shadle R, editors. ''Historical Dictionary of the British Empire'', Volume 2. page 1074 (at entry for ''Sumatra''). Greenwood Publishing Group, 1996. {{ISBN|9780313293672}}</ref>\n\n}}\n{{Coord|-3.787093|102.251848|display=title}}\n{{British overseas territories}}\n\n[[Category:British rule in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:British East India Company]]\n[[Category:Bengal Presidency]]\n[[Category:Former British colonies and protectorates in Asia|Bencoolen, British]]\n[[Category:History of Sumatra]]\n[[Category:1785 establishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1824 disestablishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1785 establishments in Asia]]\n[[Category:1824 disestablishments in Asia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox former subdivision\n|native_name = \n|common_name = Bencoolen Residency\n|nation      = British India\n|subdivision = Residency\n|era         = \n|year_start  = 1685\n|date_start  = \n|event_start = \n|year_end    = 1824\n|date_end    = \n|event_end   = [[Anglo\u2013Dutch Treaty of 1824|Anglo\u2013Dutch Treaty]]\n|event1      = \n|date_event1 = \n|p1          = \n|s1          = Dutch East Indies\n|flag_p1     = \n|flag_s1     = Flag of the Netherlands.svg \n|image_flag  = Flag of Great Britain.svg\n|image_coat  = \n|image_map   = File:IndonesiaBengkulu.png\n|image_map_caption = Location of British Bencoolen in present-day Indonesia\n|stat_area1  = \n|stat_year1  = \n|stat_pop1   = \n|today       = {{flag|Indonesia}}\n|footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''British Bencoolen''' was a British possession extending along the southwestern coast of [[Sumatra]] centered on the area of what is now [[Bengkulu City]]. The British [[East India Company]] (EIC) established a presence there in 1685,<ref name=\"Olson1996\"/> and in 1714 the EIC built [[Fort Marlborough]] there, as local datoo allowed EIC to build the fort in order to protect them from the Dutch.\n\nOriginally a [[Presidencies and Provinces of British India|Presidency]] within [[British India]], in 1785 it was downgraded to Bencoolen Residency and placed under the [[Bengal Presidency]].<ref>http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Indonesia.htm#Bencoolen</ref>\n\nOn 15 October 1817, [[Stamford Raffles]] was appointed [[Lieutenant-Governor of Bencoolen]].  During his time as Lieutenant-Governor, Raffles enacted [[Stamford Raffles#Bencoolen (Bengkulu) and Malaya|major reforms]], including the abolition of slavery, as well as creating [[Singapore]] to provide a new trading port in the region.\n\nIn 1823, Singapore was removed from the control of Bencoolen.<ref>Kevin YL Tan. [https://books.google.com/books?id=RqTwXSKrBQMC&pg=PA29&dq=%22Bencoolen%22+presidency&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7WnoUI_YH8Wn4gTshIGIAg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Bencoolen%22%20presidency&f=false ''The Singapore Legal System''].</ref> The British ceded Bencoolen to the [[Netherlands]] in the [[Anglo-Dutch Treaty of 1824]].<ref name=Roberts1>{{cite book|last=Roberts|first=Edmund|title=Embassy to the Eastern Courts of Cochin-China, Siam, and Muscat|year=1837|publisher=Harper &  Brothers|location=New York|page=34|url=http://www.wdl.org/en/item/7317/view/1/34/}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Southern Sumatra, De Grote Winkler Prins Encyclopedia 1910.jpg|thumb|Former British Bencoolen (in pink) on an 1910 map]]\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"Olson1996\">Olson JS, Shadle R, editors. ''Historical Dictionary of the British Empire'', Volume 2. page 1074 (at entry for ''Sumatra''). Greenwood Publishing Group, 1996. {{ISBN|9780313293672}}</ref>\n\n}}\n{{Coord|-3.787093|102.251848|display=title}}\n{{British overseas territories}}\n\n[[Category:British rule in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:British East India Company]]\n[[Category:Bengal Presidency]]\n[[Category:Former British colonies and protectorates in Asia|Bencoolen, British]]\n[[Category:History of Sumatra]]\n[[Category:1785 establishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1824 disestablishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1785 establishments in Asia]]\n[[Category:1824 disestablishments in Asia]]\n", "name_user": "Lubiesque", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Bencoolen"}
{"title_page": "Total Drama Island", "text_new": "{{About|the first season|the entire series|Total Drama}}\n{{pp-move-indef|small=yes}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{tone|date=October 2017}}\n{{POV|date=October 2017}}\n}}\n{{Infobox television season\t\n| bgcolour= lightgreen\t\n| image= TDIlogo.png\n| caption= The ''Total Drama Island'' logo\n| starring= {{Plainlist|<!-- featuring the voices of -->\n* [[Christian Potenza]]\n* [[Cl\u00e9 Bennett]]\n* [[Scott McCord]]\n* [[Megan Fahlenbock]]\n* [[Rachel Wilson]]\n* [[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]]\n* Novie Edwards\n* [[Dan Petronijevic]]\n* [[Stephanie Anne Mills]]\n* [[Kristin Fairlie]]\n* [[Katie Crown]]\n* [[Brian Froud (actor)|Brian Froud]]\n* [[Emilie-Claire Barlow]]\n* Lauren Lipson\n* [[Sarah Gadon]]\n* [[Peter Oldring]]\n* [[Adam Reid]]\n* [[Carter Hayden]]\n* [[Julia Chantrey]]\n}}\n| country= Canada\n| num_episodes= {{nowrap|28 (including special and review)}}\n| network= [[Teletoon]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2007|07|08}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|2008|11|29}}\n| next_season= ''[[Total Drama Action]]''\n| episode_list= List of Total Drama episodes\n}}\n'''''Total Drama Island''''' (sometimes shortened to '''''TDI''''') is a Canadian animated television series which premiered in Canada on [[Teletoon]] on July 8, 2007. This is the first season of the ''[[Total Drama]]'' series and has 26 episodes, each 22 minutes in duration<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|title=Elliott Animation - Productions - Total Drama Island|access-date=2007-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070715131925/http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|archive-date=2007-07-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> with a special 44 minute episode at the end. The season is mostly a parody of the series ''[[Survivor (TV series)|Survivor]]'', and features 22 campers in an elimination-based competition. On Cartoon Network, airing in the United States, some content has been removed from the episodes by censors in order to keep the rating open to a younger audience; for example, putting in words instead of long [[Bleep censor|bleeps]], and censoring of sensitive body parts, for the episodes \"That's Off the Chain\" and \"Trial by Tri-Armed Triathlon\". The fourth season, ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]'', takes place on the same island as this season, but with an all-new cast. ''Total Drama Island'' was created by [[Tom McGillis]] and [[Jennifer Pertsch]] with their production studio, [[Fresh TV]], which also created their previous animated series, ''[[6teen]]''.\n\n==Plot==\n[[File:TDIsland.png|thumb|right|A grand view of the main setting used in this season (which is artificially recreated in the [[Total Drama Action|next season]]). The island is also used in [[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island|the fourth]] and [[Total Drama All-Stars and Pahkitew Island|fifth season]]s (which leads to its destruction).]]\n''Total Drama Island'' is set in the fictional titular reality show, which follows the competition of 22 unsuspecting and unknowing teenagers at Camp Wawanakwa, the most rundown, bug-infested, disgusting island located in an unspecified area in [[Muskoka]], [[Ontario]]. The campers participate in competitions and challenges which get more insane and dangerous each week to avoid being voted off the island by their fellow campers and teammates. At the end of the series, the winning contestant will receive {{currency|100,000|CAD}} AND DO SEX. The competition is hosted by Chris McLean, assisted by the camp's chef, Chef Hatchet, who is also Chris' best friend despite being mistreated at times. Egotistical and immoral, unless something affects him legally, Chris places the show's contestants in various life-threatening challenges.\n\nAt the beginning of the season, the twenty-two 16-year-old campers are placed into two groups of eleven, the \"Screaming Gophers\" and the \"Killer Bass\". In each episode, the teams participate in HAVING SEX AND a challenge, in which one or more campers can win invincibility for their team. The losing team is called to the campfire that night, where they vote one of their members off the island. The camper with the most votes is eliminated from the competition. At this campfire, McLean passes out marshmallows to the campers who have not been voted off, while the one who does not get a marshmallow must walk down the Dock of Shame to the Boat of Losers, which will take them away from the island and they will \"never, never, never, ever, ever, ever, come back, ever\" according to Chris (this was proved a lie in \"No Pain, No Game\", when he brought Eva and Izzy back into the game).\n\nAbout halfway through the season, the teams are disbanded, so it is every camper for themselves, after which the challenges continue; the winner of each challenge then only receives invincibility AND DO PORN for him or herself, whereupon the rest of the campers vote one camper without invincibility off the island. This process of elimination continued on until two players remain on the island. These two players were then subject to a final contest. ''Total Drama Island'' is a parody of the reality show ''[[Survivor (franchise)|Survivor]]''. Host Chris McLean is very similar to ''Survivor'' host [[Jeff Probst]].<ref name = \"monitor\">{{Citation| author = Aaron Sagers| title = Pop 20: If Facebook were a dinner party| newspaper = The Monitor| issue =| page =| date = September 1, 2009}}</ref> This is the first season in which the winner does not get to keep the money, due to it being eaten by a shark in the episode \"Total Drama Drama Drama Drama Island\".\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Total Drama Island episodes}}\n''Total Drama Island'' is a Canadian animated television series which premiered on July 8, 2007, on the [[Teletoon]] channel. This season has 26 episodes, each 22 minutes in duration, and two special episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|title=Elliott Animation \u2013 Productions \u2013 Total Drama Island|access-date=2007-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070715131925/http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|archive-date=2007-07-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was the third Cartoon Network show outside of [[Adult Swim]] and [[Toonami]] to have the [[TV Parental Guidelines|U.S. rating]] of either \"TV-PG\" or \"TV-PG-D\", and a parental-guidance warning after every commercial break and at the beginning of the show (the first two being ''[[Sunday Pants]]'' and ''[[IGPX]]''). Its rating in Canada was initially \"[[Television content rating systems#English ratings|G]]\" while current broadcasts are rated \"[[Television content rating systems#English ratings|PG]]\".\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:60px\"| Season\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:70px\"| Episodes\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:120px\"| Country\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:120px\"| Network\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:140px\"| First air date\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:140px\"| Last air date\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 27<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/shows/total-drama-island/episodes/|title=Total Drama Island|work=TV.com|accessdate=5 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619140523/http://www.tv.com/shows/total-drama-island/episodes/|archive-date=19 June 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| Canada\n| [[Teletoon]]\n| July 8, 2007\n| November 29, 2008\n|-\n| United States\n| [[Cartoon Network]]\n| June 5, 2008\n| December 18, 2008\n|-\n| United Kingdom\n| [[Jetix]]\n| April 1, 2009\n| May 6, 2009\n|}\n\n==Characters==\n[[File:TDCast1.png|thumb|right|<center>'''The primary cast of ''Total Drama Island''.'''</center><hr />'''Top:''' DJ, Duncan, Tyler, Harold, Geoff, and Heather<hr />'''Middle:''' Lindsay, Leshawna, Eva, Justin, Owen, Noah, Trent, Gwen, and Cody<hr />'''Sitting:''' Izzy, Bridgette, Courtney, Katie, Sadie, Ezekiel, and Beth]]\n\n===Staff===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=text-align:center\n|-\n! Character\n! Voice actor\n! Description\n|-\n| {{va|Chris McLean}}\n| [[Christian Potenza]]\n| Chris is the host of the series.\n|-\n| {{va|Chef Hatchet}}\n| [[Cl\u00e9 Bennett]]\n| Hatchet is the cook and co-host of the series.\n|-\n|}\n\n===Contestants===\nThere are 22 original contestants who competed in ''Total Drama Island''. They are Beth, Bridgette, Cody, Courtney, DJ, Duncan, Eva, Ezekiel, Geoff, Gwen, Harold, Heather, Izzy, Justin, Katie, Leshawna, Lindsay, Noah, Owen, Sadie, Trent, and Tyler. Many of the characters return in later seasons either as contestants or as guests.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center\"\n|+List of ''Total Drama Island'' contestants\n!align=\"left\"|Contestant\n!Original team\n!Merge\n!Finish\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Ezekiel''' <br /><small>The Home Schooled Guy</small>\n|{{stribe|chapera|Killer Bass}}\n| style=\"background:darkgrey;\" rowspan=\"12\"|\n|{{sort|16|22nd place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Eva''\n|{{stribe|chapera|Killer Bass}}\n|''Returned to game''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Noah'''<br /><small>The Schemer</small>\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|Screaming Gophers}}\n|{{sort|14|21st place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Justin'''<br /><small>The Eye Candy</small>\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|Screaming Gophers}}\n|{{sort|13|20th place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Katie'''<br /><small>The Sweet Girl</small>\n|{{stribe|chapera|Killer Bass}}{{efn|This contestant was originally on the Screaming Gophers, but was switched over to the Killer Bass due to Izzy voluteering to switch.}}\n|{{sort|12|19th place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Tyler'''<br /><small>The Jock</small>\n|{{stribe|chapera|Killer Bass}}\n|{{sort|11|18th place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Izzy''\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|Screaming Gophers}}\n|{{sort|6|Left{{efn|