\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| {{stribe|chabogamogo|}}\n|bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"| IN\n|bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"| OUT\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=11|\n|-\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray|\n|Eva\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=11|\n|bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"| OUT\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=12|\n|-\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Harold\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|LOW}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|LOW}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|LOW}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=14|\n|-\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Courtney\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|LOW}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|LOW}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=15|\n|-\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Sadie\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|LOW}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=16|\n|-\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Beth\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=17|\n|-\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Cody\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=18|\n|-\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Tyler\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=20|\n|-\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Katie\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n| bgcolor=salmon|\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=21|\n|-\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Justin\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=22|\n|-\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n| {{stribe|mogomogo|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Noah\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|IN}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n| bgcolor=lightgreen|\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=23|\n|-\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n| {{stribe|chapera|}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=2|\n|Ezekiel\n|{{stribe|chapera|IN}}\n|{{stribe|chapera|OUT}}\n|bgcolor=darkgray colspan=25|\n|}\n\n==Production==\n''Total Drama Island'' was developed and produced by [[Fresh TV]], starting in 2006, with an early name for the series being ''Camp TV''.<ref name=\"camptv\">{{Citation| url = http://coldhardflash.com/2006/03/neptoons-promo-washes-ashore.html| title = Neptoon's Promo Washes Ashore| author = admin| work = Cold Hard Flash| date = March 27, 2006| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060510060119/http://www.coldhardflash.com/2006/03/neptoons-promo-washes-ashore.html| archive-date = May 10, 2006| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> The season was animated at Elliott Animation and was directed by Todd Kauffman and Mark Thornton.<ref name=\"production\">{{Citation| url = http://coldhardflash.com/2007/06/title-drama-island.html| title = Title Drama Island| author = admin| work = Cold Hard Flash| date = June 29, 2007| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080717025321/http://coldhardflash.com/2007/06/title-drama-island.html| archive-date = July 17, 2008| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> It was primarily targeted at eight-to-twelve-year-olds, and the creators, [[Tom McGillis]] and [[Jennifer Pertsch]], studied what [[tween]]s liked and disliked about [[reality television|reality television shows]] in the writing process.<ref name=\"likes\">{{Citation| url = http://www.playbackmag.com/articles/magazine/20060515/dramaisland.html| title = Total Drama Island ribs reality TV| author = Playback Staff | work = Playback| date = May 15, 2006| accessdate = December 25, 2010}}</ref> McGillis said that they used a \"countrywide online research project\" to determine this demographic's likes.<ref name=\"thestar\">{{Citation| author = Raju Mudhar| url = https://www.thestar.com/article/568536| title = Canadian cartoon show sucking 'em all back in| newspaper = The Toronto Star| accessdate = December 25, 2010| date = January 11, 2009| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101005014309/http://www.thestar.com/article/568536| archive-date = October 5, 2010| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> Fresh TV Inc. partners McGillis, Pertsch, Elliott and [[Brian Irving|Irving]] produced the series.<ref name=\"itbegins\">{{Citation| url = http://totaldramaisland.blogspot.com/2006/07/and-so-it-begins.html| title = Total Drama Island: And So It Begins| author = Playback Staff | date = May 15, 2006| accessdate = December 25, 2010}}</ref> The budget for the series was [[US$|$]]8 million.<ref name=\"budget\">{{Citation| url = http://canali.kataweb.it/kataweb-guardaconme/2010/02/21/lisola-di-cartone-che-prende-in-giro-i-reality/| title = L'Isola di cartone che prende in giro i reality| author = Annalisa D'Aprile| language = Italian| work = Kata Web| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100514063848/http://canali.kataweb.it/kataweb-guardaconme/2010/02/21/lisola-di-cartone-che-prende-in-giro-i-reality/| archive-date = May 14, 2010| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> It was animated in [[Adobe Flash|Flash]],<ref name = \"production\"/> at Elliott Animation's studio in Toronto.<ref name=\"itbegins\"/> Every cast and crew member on ''Total Drama Island'' had to sign a [[confidentiality agreement]] not to disclose who the winner was.<ref name=\"secret\">{{Citation| url = http://www.channelcanada.com/Article1894.html| title = From the creators of the award winning series 6teen, the number one show on Teletoon, comes a truly unique reality show for kids| work = Channel Canada| author = Teletoon| date = Jun 24, 2007| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081228225728/http://www.channelcanada.com/Article1894.html| archive-date = December 28, 2008| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> All the characters were designed by Kauffman.<ref name=\"Final 4\">[http://totaldramaisland.blogspot.com/2007/11/final-4.html Total Drama Island: Final 4]{{dead link|date=December 2010}}</ref> Voice actors from the FreshTV series ''[[6teen]]'' have lent their voices for ''Total Drama Island'': [[Christian Potenza]], who played the character Jude on ''6teen'', played the role of host [[List of Total Drama characters#Chris McLean|Chris McLean]]. Potenza said that the best part of the job was that his character could not be voted off the show.<ref name = \"potenza\">{{Citation| url = | title = Newest role is 'every guy's dream' \u2013 Gemini-nominated Oakville actor has written his own dream role| author = Krissie Rutherford| work = Oakville Beaver| date = November 3, 2006}}</ref> [[Emilie-Claire Barlow]] plays a recurring role as Chrissy on ''6teen'' and plays Courtney on ''Total Drama Island''. Barlow stated that Courtney was her favorite character that she had ever played.<ref name=\"barlow\">{{Citation| url = https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/1224829331.html?dids=1224829331:1224829331&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Mar+1%2C+2007&author=Asma+Khaliq&pub=Toronto+Star&edition=&startpage=P.8&desc=Up+close+with+a+familiar+voice%3B+From+Sailor+Mars+to+Timmy%27s+ads%2C+Emilie-Claire+Barlow+is+someone+you%27ve+definitely+heard| title = Up close with a familiar voice: From Sailor Mars to Timmy's ads, Emilie-Claire Barlow is someone you've definitely heard| author = Asma Khaliq| work = The Toronto Star| date = March 1, 2007| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090813043947/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/1224829331.html?dids=1224829331:1224829331&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Mar+1%2C+2007&author=Asma+Khaliq&pub=Toronto+Star&edition=&startpage=P.8&desc=Up+close+with+a+familiar+voice%3B+From+Sailor+Mars+to+Timmy%27s+ads%2C+Emilie-Claire+Barlow+is+someone+you%27ve+definitely+heard| archive-date = August 13, 2009| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> Other voice actors from ''6teen'' include Julia Chantrey as [[List of Total Drama characters#Eva|Eva]]; [[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]] (Kai) as [[List of Total Drama characters#Duncan|Duncan]]; [[Megan Fahlenbock]] (Jen) as [[List of Total Drama characters#Gwen|Gwen]]; [[Adam Reid]] (Wayne) as [[List of Total Drama characters#Justin|Justin]]; [[Stephanie Anne Mills]] (Kirsten) as [[List of Total Drama characters#Lindsay|Lindsay]] and [[List of Total Drama characters#Katie|Katie]]; and [[Rachel Wilson]] (Melinda Wilson) as [[List of Total Drama characters#Heather|Heather]].\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\nCarole Bonneau, the Vice President of programming of Teletoon Canada stated that ''Total Drama Island'', along with Fresh TV's ''6teen'' were \"consistently top performers\" for audiences of ages 6\u201311, and also helped to bring in older viewers as well.<ref name=\"ratings1\">{{Citation| url = http://www.mediaincanada.com/articles/mic/20080206/teletoon.html| title = Teletoon orders new series for fall| work = Media in Canada| accessdate = December 22, 2010}}</ref> When ''Total Drama Island'' aired on the American Cartoon Network, it performed very well; ''The Toronto Star'' reported that, \"in some ages groups [''Total Drama Island'' showed] a 500 per cent ratings increase in [its] time slot.\"<ref name=\"thestar\"/> On December 11, 2008, ''Total Drama Island'' garnered 3.5 million viewers.<ref name=\"ratings3\">{{Citation| url = https://www.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2008-12-16-nielsens-analysis_N.htm| title = Nielsens: Dallas, 'Boston' score key ratings wins| work = USA Today| author = Gary Levin| date = December 18, 2008| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090208203657/http://www.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2008-12-16-nielsens-analysis_N.htm| archive-date = February 8, 2009| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> That year, the series was the top \"regularly scheduled Thursday night program at 9 p.m. on all television throughout third quarter among boys 2-11, 6-11 and 9-14,\" according to the ''Animation World Network''.<ref name=\"ratings4\">{{Citation| url = http://www.awn.com/news/television/ratings-highlights-cartoon-network-disney-channel-nickelodeon| title = Ratings Highlights For Cartoon Network, Disney Channel, Nickelodeon| work = Animation World Network| author = Annemarie Moody| date = October 2, 2008| accessdate = December 26, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20091212033944/http://www.awn.com/news/television/ratings-highlights-cartoon-network-disney-channel-nickelodeon| archive-date = December 12, 2009| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> On Memorial Day weekend of 2009, a marathon of ''Total Drama Island'' increased viewership in age groups 2-11, 6-11, and 9-14, each by 20% or more compared to the same week in 2008.<ref name=\"ratings2\">{{Citation| url = http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/05/27/cartoon-networks-total-drama-island-earns-double-digit-increases/19452| title = Cartoon Network's Total Drama Island Earns Double Digit Increases| work = TV by the Numbers| author = Bill Gorman| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121025233123/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/05/27/cartoon-networks-total-drama-island-earns-double-digit-increases/19452/| archive-date = October 25, 2012| url-status = live| df = mdy-all| date = 2009-05-27}}</ref> As of 2011, ''Total Drama Island'' has aired in over 188 countries.<ref>{{cite news|last=Stinson|first=Scott|title=Stinson: CanCon on the Croisette at Mipcom|url=http://arts.nationalpost.com/2011/10/13/stinson-cancon-on-the-croisette-at-mipcom/|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20111014185212/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2011/10/13/stinson-cancon-on-the-croisette-at-mipcom/|url-status=dead|archive-date=14 October 2011|accessdate=14 October 2011|newspaper=The Globe and Mail|date=13 October 2011|location=Toronto ON}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reaction===\n''Total Drama Island'' has received critical acclaim. Common Sense Media gave the show 4 out of 5 stars, calling it a \"[c]lever cartoon reality show spoof\", even though it also describes it as too intense for young children to watch.<ref name=\"ratings5\">{{Citation| url = http://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/total-drama-island| title = Total Drama Island| work = Common Sense Media| accessdate = December 22, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100526092052/http://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/total-drama-island| archive-date = May 26, 2010| url-status = live| df = mdy-all| date = 2008-06-06}}</ref> The series was nominated for a Gemini Award for \"Best Animated Program or Series\", shared by Tom McGillis, Jennifer Pertsch, George Elliott and Brian Irving.<ref name=\"gemini\">{{Citation | url = http://www.channelcanada.com/Article2419.html | title = Fresh TV Inc. Celebrates Three Gemini Nominations for Top Rated Shows | accessdate = 2009-03-21 | work = www.channelcanada.com | publisher = ChannelCanada.com | date = 2008-08-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090805170006/http://www.channelcanada.com/Article2419.html | archive-date = 2009-08-05 | url-status = live }}</ref> Debi Enker of ''[[The Age]]'' gave a negative review of the season's last episode, calling the art, design and writing \"lamentable.\"<ref name = \"theage\">{{Citation| author = Debi Enker| title = Total Drama Island| newspaper = The Age| issue = | page = 36| date = June 10, 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Public reaction===\n''Total Drama Island'' received a score of 8.2 on [[Metacritic]] from users.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/total-drama-island/user-reviews|title=Read User Reviews and Submit your own for Total Drama Island - Metacritic|accessdate=5 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905195130/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/total-drama-island/user-reviews|archive-date=5 September 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Media==\n===DVD releases===\nA DVD was released by [[Warner Home Video]] and Cartoon Network on August 18, 2009 in the United States. It contains all of the 27 episodes (including TDI Rundown) of season one of this series in a 4 disc set, for a total of 594 minutes long. In addition, its bonus features (entitled as X-tras) are the audition tapes of twenty two campers, as well as Izzy's second audition tape and her exclusive interview with Chris. In Australia, ''Total Drama Island'' is on Region 4 DVD as separate volumes. This series of discs contains the widescreen version with uncut scenes and original dialogue, as seen on Teletoon and [[ABC3]]. In reviewing the DVD for season, Matthew Price of ''The Oklahoman'' wrote that while the show started out \"unbelievably slowly,\" the series became more interesting as campers began getting voted off. Price also praised the parody of reality shows.<ref name = \"oknews\">{{Citation| author = Matthew Price| title = DVD Reviews| newspaper = The Oklahoman| issue = | page = | date = September 25, 2009 }}</ref> In another review of the DVD, Jeffrey Kauffman of ''[[DVD Talk]]'' wrote that the character development was compelling and that the parody of reality shows were very funny.<ref name=\"dvdtalk\">{{Citation| author = Jeffrey Kauffman| title = Total Drama Island: The Complete Series| url = http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/38285/total-drama-island-the-complete-series/?___rd=1| date = August 18, 2009| work = DVD Talk| accessdate = December 25, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150619225951/http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/38285/total-drama-island-the-complete-series/?___rd=1| archive-date = June 19, 2015| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> Mac McEntire of ''[[DVD Verdict]]'' praised the character development as well, but noted that the show sometimes sinks to \"lowbrow gross-outs\".<ref name=\"dvdverict\">{{Citation| author = Mac McEntire| title = Total Drama Island: The Complete Series| url = http://www.dvdverdict.com/reviews/totaldramaisland.php| work = DVD Verdict| date = August 19, 2009| accessdate = December 26, 2010| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101031004020/http://www.dvdverdict.com/reviews/totaldramaisland.php| archivedate = October 31, 2010}}</ref> Both Kauffman and McEntire recommended the series DVD.\n\n===Total Drama Island Interactive===\n''Total Drama Island'' Interactive was an online game in Canada marketed in conjunction with the television series. It was produced by [[Xenophile Media]]. By registering a free account, the player could play games using a customizable [[Avatar (computing)|avatar]] to earn points for marshmallows. Marshmallows are used as money in the game so the player can buy in-game items. The player who earned the most points had their avatar make a cameo appearance in the season finale.<ref name=\"interactive\">{{Citation| author =| url =| title = Xenophile Media and Fresh TV Receive International Interactive Emmy(R) Award Nomination for Total Drama Island \u2013 Totally Interactive!| work = Canada Newswire| date = March 6, 2008}}</ref> The games were based on the challenges in the show.<ref name=\"bellfund\">{{Citation| url = http://www.ipf.ca/Bell/publications_PDF/BF_REPORT_2006.pdf| title = BellFund Annual Report: 2006| work = BellFund| year = 2006| accessdate = December 26, 2010| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101212014325/http://www.ipf.ca/Bell/publications_PDF/BF_REPORT_2006.pdf| archivedate = December 12, 2010}}</ref> ''Total Drama Island'' Interactive was nominated for an Interactive Emmy Award in 2007.<ref name=\"interactive\"/> However, the website is currently no longer available, as it has been replaced by Total Drama Online and by the Teletoon official site.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.totaldramaonline.com/|title=ACCUEIL - teletoon.com|accessdate=5 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081028202209/http://www.totaldramaonline.com/|archivedate=28 October 2008}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Television|Canada}}\n{{Portal bar|Animation|Television|Canada}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*[http://www.totaldramaisland.blogspot.com/ Official ''Total Drama Island'' blog]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070714223523/http://tdi.teletoon.com/index.php?TeletoonLangID=en ''Total Drama Island'' Interactive]\n*[http://www.totaldramaisland.com totaldramaisland.com]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090420020918/http://www.freshtvinc.com/news/news_details.asp?c=1&id=24 Fresh TV announces ''Total Drama: The Musical'']\n*{{IMDb title|1173427|Total Drama Island}}\n*{{tv.com show|total-drama-island|Total Drama Island}}\n\n{{Total Drama}}\n\n[[Category:Total Drama seasons]]\n[[Category:2007 Canadian television seasons]]\n[[Category:2008 Canadian television seasons]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2000s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2000s Canadian satirical television series]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Canadian flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian mockumentary television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated musical television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the first season|the entire series|Total Drama}}\n{{pp-move-indef|small=yes}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{tone|date=October 2017}}\n{{POV|date=October 2017}}\n}}\n{{Infobox television season\t\n| bgcolour= lightgreen\t\n| image= TDIlogo.png\n| caption= The ''Total Drama Island'' logo\n| starring= {{Plainlist|<!-- featuring the voices of -->\n* [[Christian Potenza]]\n* [[Cl\u00e9 Bennett]]\n* [[Scott McCord]]\n* [[Megan Fahlenbock]]\n* [[Rachel Wilson]]\n* [[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]]\n* Novie Edwards\n* [[Dan Petronijevic]]\n* [[Stephanie Anne Mills]]\n* [[Kristin Fairlie]]\n* [[Katie Crown]]\n* [[Brian Froud (actor)|Brian Froud]]\n* [[Emilie-Claire Barlow]]\n* Lauren Lipson\n* [[Sarah Gadon]]\n* [[Peter Oldring]]\n* [[Adam Reid]]\n* [[Carter Hayden]]\n* [[Julia Chantrey]]\n}}\n| country= Canada\n| num_episodes= {{nowrap|28 (including special and review)}}\n| network= [[Teletoon]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2007|07|08}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|2008|11|29}}\n| next_season= ''[[Total Drama Action]]''\n| episode_list= List of Total Drama episodes\n}}\n'''''Total Drama Island''''' (sometimes shortened to '''''TDI''''') is a Canadian animated television series which premiered in Canada on [[Teletoon]] on July 8, 2007. This is the first season of the ''[[Total Drama]]'' series and has 26 episodes, each 22 minutes in duration<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|title=Elliott Animation - Productions - Total Drama Island|access-date=2007-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070715131925/http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|archive-date=2007-07-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> with a special 44 minute episode at the end. The season is mostly a parody of the series ''[[Survivor (TV series)|Survivor]]'', and features 22 campers in an elimination-based competition. On Cartoon Network, airing in the United States, some content has been removed from the episodes by censors in order to keep the rating open to a younger audience; for example, putting in words instead of long [[Bleep censor|bleeps]], and censoring of sensitive body parts, for the episodes \"That's Off the Chain\" and \"Trial by Tri-Armed Triathlon\". The fourth season, ''[[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island]]'', takes place on the same island as this season, but with an all-new cast. ''Total Drama Island'' was created by [[Tom McGillis]] and [[Jennifer Pertsch]] with their production studio, [[Fresh TV]], which also created their previous animated series, ''[[6teen]]''.\n\n==Plot==\n[[File:TDIsland.png|thumb|right|A grand view of the main setting used in this season (which is artificially recreated in the [[Total Drama Action|next season]]). The island is also used in [[Total Drama: Revenge of the Island|the fourth]] and [[Total Drama All-Stars and Pahkitew Island|fifth season]]s (which leads to its destruction).]]\n''Total Drama Island'' is set in the fictional titular reality show, which follows the competition of 22 unsuspecting and unknowing teenagers at Camp Wawanakwa, the most rundown, bug-infested, disgusting island located in an unspecified area in [[Muskoka]], [[Ontario]]. The campers participate in competitions and challenges which get more insane and dangerous each week to avoid being voted off the island by their fellow campers and teammates. At the end of the series, the winning contestant will receive {{currency|100,000|CAD}}. The competition is hosted by Chris McLean, assisted by the camp's chef, Chef Hatchet, who is also Chris' best friend despite being mistreated at times. Egotistical and immoral, unless something affects him legally, Chris places the show's contestants in various life-threatening challenges.\n\nAt the beginning of the season, the twenty-two 16-year-old campers are placed into two groups of eleven, the \"Screaming Gophers\" and the \"Killer Bass\". In each episode, the teams participate in a challenge, in which one or more campers can win invincibility for their team. The losing team is called to the campfire that night, where they vote one of their members off the island. The camper with the most votes is eliminated from the competition. At this campfire, McLean passes out marshmallows to the campers who have not been voted off, while the one who does not get a marshmallow must walk down the Dock of Shame to the Boat of Losers, which will take them away from the island and they will \"never, never, never, ever, ever, ever, come back, ever\" according to Chris (this was proved a lie in \"No Pain, No Game\", when he brought Eva and Izzy back into the game).\n\nAbout halfway through the season, the teams are disbanded, so it is every camper for themselves, after which the challenges continue; the winner of each challenge then only receives invincibility for him or herself, whereupon the rest of the campers vote one camper without invincibility off the island. This process of elimination continued on until two players remain on the island. These two players were then subject to a final contest. ''Total Drama Island'' is a parody of the reality show ''[[Survivor (franchise)|Survivor]]''. Host Chris McLean is very similar to ''Survivor'' host [[Jeff Probst]].<ref name = \"monitor\">{{Citation| author = Aaron Sagers| title = Pop 20: If Facebook were a dinner party| newspaper = The Monitor| issue =| page =| date = September 1, 2009}}</ref> This is the first season in which the winner does not get to keep the money, due to it being eaten by a shark in the episode \"Total Drama Drama Drama Drama Island\".\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Total Drama Island episodes}}\n''Total Drama Island'' is a Canadian animated television series which premiered on July 8, 2007, on the [[Teletoon]] channel. This season has 26 episodes, each 22 minutes in duration, and two special episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|title=Elliott Animation \u2013 Productions \u2013 Total Drama Island|access-date=2007-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070715131925/http://www.elliottanimation.com/productions/totaldramaisland/details.htm|archive-date=2007-07-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was the third Cartoon Network show outside of [[Adult Swim]] and [[Toonami]] to have the [[TV Parental Guidelines|U.S. rating]] of either \"TV-PG\" or \"TV-PG-D\", and a parental-guidance warning after every commercial break and at the beginning of the show (the first two being ''[[Sunday Pants]]'' and ''[[IGPX]]''). Its rating in Canada was initially \"[[Television content rating systems#English ratings|G]]\" while current broadcasts are rated \"[[Television content rating systems#English ratings|PG]]\".\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:60px\"| Season\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:70px\"| Episodes\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:120px\"| Country\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:120px\"| Network\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:140px\"| First air date\n! style=\"background:lightgreen;width:140px\"| Last air date\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 27<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/shows/total-drama-island/episodes/|title=Total Drama Island|work=TV.com|accessdate=5 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619140523/http://www.tv.com/shows/total-drama-island/episodes/|archive-date=19 June 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| Canada\n| [[Teletoon]]\n| July 8, 2007\n| November 29, 2008\n|-\n| United States\n| [[Cartoon Network]]\n| June 5, 2008\n| December 18, 2008\n|-\n| United Kingdom\n| [[Jetix]]\n| April 1, 2009\n| May 6, 2009\n|}\n\n==Characters==\n[[File:TDCast1.png|thumb|right|<center>'''The primary cast of ''Total Drama Island''.'''</center><hr />'''Top:''' DJ, Duncan, Tyler, Harold, Geoff, and Heather<hr />'''Middle:''' Lindsay, Leshawna, Eva, Justin, Owen, Noah, Trent, Gwen, and Cody<hr />'''Sitting:''' Izzy, Bridgette, Courtney, Katie, Sadie, Ezekiel, and Beth]]\n\n===Staff===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=text-align:center\n|-\n! Character\n! Voice actor\n! Description\n|-\n| {{va|Chris McLean}}\n| [[Christian Potenza]]\n| Chris is the host of the series.\n|-\n| {{va|Chef Hatchet}}\n| [[Cl\u00e9 Bennett]]\n| Hatchet is the cook and co-host of the series.\n|-\n|}\n\n===Contestants===\nThere are 22 original contestants who competed in ''Total Drama Island''. They are Beth, Bridgette, Cody, Courtney, DJ, Duncan, Eva, Ezekiel, Geoff, Gwen, Harold, Heather, Izzy, Justin, Katie, Leshawna, Lindsay, Noah, Owen, Sadie, Trent, and Tyler. Many of the characters return in later seasons either as contestants or as guests.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center\"\n|+List of ''Total Drama Island'' contestants\n!align=\"left\"|Contestant\n!Original team\n!Merge\n!Finish\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Ezekiel''' <br /><small>The Home Schooled Guy</small>\n|{{stribe|chapera|Killer Bass}}\n| style=\"background:darkgrey;\" rowspan=\"12\"|\n|{{sort|16|22nd place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Eva''\n|{{stribe|chapera|Killer Bass}}\n|''Returned to game''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Noah'''<br /><small>The Schemer</small>\n|{{stribe|mogomogo|Screaming Gophers}}\n|{{sort|14|21st place}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''Justin'''<br /><sma